comfortable enough in his mind to realize there was no potential 
for anything that he dairy or agriculture committee was going to 
pass that was going to impact directly on that investment 
no law or rule prevents members of congress from holding assets 
that might conflict with their official duties they are free to 
craft and vote on legislation that could affect their financial 
interests 
white house officials and other executive branch employees on 
the other hand are barred under the basic federal conflict of 
interest law from taking government action in which they or their 
immediate family has a financial interest unless they obtain a 
waiver the top penalty is two years in prison and a 10000 fine 
in 1985 coelho and thenrep james jeffords rvt introduced 
a bill that among other things would pay farmers not to produce 
milk at a time the industry was beset with surpluses 
